Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Sweet Potato{1%unit} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Put the sweet potato chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over half the @Cajun Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pour the @Water for the Rice{300%ml} into a medium #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, halve the @Green Pepper{1%unit} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced Chorizo{90%g} and pepper chunks and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and golden, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1%unit} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @Red Kidney Beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}. Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}.

Once the pepper has softened, stir in the garlic and remaining Cajun spice mix and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @BBQ Sauce{32%g}, kidney beans, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{150%ml} (see pantry for both amounts) to the pan, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir together, then bring to a simmer and cook until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Once thickened, stir the roasted sweet potato through the chilli.

Add a splash of @water{} to loosen if you feel it needs it. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your #bowls{} and spoon the chorizo and sweet potato chilli over the top.

Finish with a dollop of @Soured Cream{75%g} and a sprinkle of cheese.

Enjoy!